CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 13, 1965, pg. 24 reads: City Champs - Smiles were the order of the day at the Pitt Field House, last Friday afternoon , as Schenley High School celebrated winning the city high school basketball championship, against South Hills. Shown left, is Archie McGill, with Coach Fisher and Melvin Snowden, third row, fourth from left, James Prince, in back row, with ball, is Kenny Durrett. - Harris Photo.
TitMainTitle: Schenley High School basketball team, from left, front row: Anthony Austin, Edward "Petey" Gibson, and #20 Kimberly Owens; second row: Thomas Carroll, Charles Burley, Jr., Archie McGill, Coach Willard Fisher, Marvin Snowden, and Clarence Montgomery; third row: #10 unknown, Richard Harper, Steven Horne, #54 Kenneth "Kenny" Durrett holding ball, James Prince, Frank Williams wearing suit, and William Ford, cheering in locker room after winning championship title, Pitt Field House
